Explanation:
We use a 26-element array to store the count of each character. Iterate through the string and update the count for each character. If the count exceeds 2, decrement it. Finally, keep track of the maximum length of a substring by updating maxLength with the length of the substring from the current index to the first occurrence of a character with count greater than 2.

